title: Biden interrupted by protesters more than a dozen times at campaign rally
description: Anti-war protesters shouted at President Joe Biden during his speech on abortion rights.

title: Turkey lawmakers sign off on Sweden's NATO membership, lifting key a hurdle
description: ANKARA, Turkey — Turkish legislators on Tuesday endorsed Sweden’s membership in NATO, lifting a major hurdle on the previously nonaligned country’s entry into the military alliance.

title: Gazans dig multiple graves at Khan Younis hospital
description: Dozens of bodies had to be buried in sandy graves on the grounds of the al-Nasser Hospital in Khan Younis as the Israeli military offensive made traveling to the cemetery too dangerous.

title: Torture allegations spiked in Israeli jails after Oct. 7, as one group warns jailers seek 'revenge'
description: Abuses against Palestinians held in Israeli jails have risen since Hamas' Oct. 7 attacks, former detainees and rights organizations have warned.

title: Atomic scientists keep ‘Doomsday Clock’ as close to midnight as ever
description: Atomic scientists kept their “Doomsday Clock” set at 90 seconds to midnight, citing threats from multiple wars, nuclear weapons and climate change as factors.

title: Doomsday Clock stays at 90 seconds to midnight for second straight year
description: The Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists has kept the Doomsday Clock set to 90 seconds to midnight for the second straight year, largely attributed to the war in Ukraine, the Israel-Hamas war and the threat of artificial intelligence.  The clock is a symbolic indication of humanity’s perceived proximity to human-caused catastrophe.

title: Russian missile strikes kill at least 5 people in Kharkiv
description: Russian missiles struck three Ukrainian cities including Kharkiv, killing at least seven people total and wrecking apartment buildings.

title: Gerard Depardieu sexual assault complaint dismissed by French prosecutors due to statute of limitations
description: French prosecutors have dismissed the complaint filed by French actor Hélène Darras alleging that Gerard Depardieu sexually assaulted her during the filming of “Disco” in 2007.

title: Russian missiles strike Ukrainian cities again, killing at least 6 and wounding dozens
description: Russian missiles struck three Ukrainian cities Tuesday, including its two biggest, killing at least six people and wrecking apartment buildings after Moscow shunned any deal backed by Kyiv and its Western allies to end the nearly 2-year-old war.

title: Kyiv residents seek shelter in a subway station amid Russian attacks
description: Residents in Kyiv sought shelter in a subway station amid Russian missile attacks on the city. Seven people in the capital’s districts were injured in the bombardment.

title: U.S. and British militaries launch new strikes against Houthi sites in Yemen
description: According to officials, the U.S. and U.K. used warship- and submarine-launched Tomahawk missiles and fighter jets to take out Houthi missile storage sites, drones and launchers. It's the second time the two allies have conducted coordinated retaliatory strikes.

title: Taliban is enforcing restrictions on single and unaccompanied Afghan women, U.N. says
description: The Taliban are restricting Afghan women’s access to work, travel and health care if they are unmarried or don’t have a male guardian, a U.N report said.

title: Six nuns kidnapped in Haiti amid rise in gang violence
description: Hours after families of hostages stormed a parliamentary committee meeting to demand action from the government, Israeli officials told NBC News that they proposed a two-month pause in the war in exchange for the release of hostages in Gaza.

title: U.S. and U.K. launch more strikes against Iranian-backed militia
description: For the second time, the U.S. and U.K. have launched strikes against the Houthi militia, who has been terrorizing ships in the Red Sea. U.S. Centcom says they struck 8 Houthi targets inside Yemen.
